snippet: Jan Bakelants outsprinted Lieuwe Westra to win the sixth stage of the Critérium du Dauphiné in France, while Chris Froome survived a crash to keep the overall lead by 12 seconds, ahead of Alberto Contador.
lead_paragraph: Jan Bakelants outsprinted Lieuwe Westra to win the sixth stage of the Critérium du Dauphiné in France, while Chris Froome survived a crash to keep the overall lead by 12 seconds, ahead of Alberto Contador.

headline.main: Contador Still Trails in France After Stage 6
